question: Determine the individual who founded Microsoft and use their birthplace to identify the founder of a major aerospace enterprise established in that same city during 1916 that remains a leading global sector company; subsequently, determine the birthplace associated with this referenced individual and use it to identify the transformative industrial innovator who established a foundational manufacturing enterprise in that city during the early twentieth century and remains iconic for revolutionizing production methodologies.
subject: web_search
derived_ev: Microsoft was founded by Bill Gates and Paul Allen to market BASIC interpreters for the Altair 8800, as confirmed by Wikipedia and Microsoft's official historical announcement
Microsoft was founded on April 4, 1975 by Bill Gates and Paul Allen according to History.com's historical records
The founder of Microsoft is Bill Gates
Bill Gates was born on October 28, 1955 in Seattle, Washington according to authoritative sources including Wikipedia, HistoryLink.org, and Britannica

Boeing was founded in Seattle in 1916 and remains one of the city's most significant global enterprises based on Washington State historical records and Seattle Metropolitan Chamber of Commerce materials
William E. Boeing personally established Pacific Aero Products Co. in 1916, which later became The Boeing Company
William E. Boeing was born on October 1, 1881 in Detroit, Michigan according to Boeing's official corporate history and Encyclopedia Britannica

Henry Ford established Ford Motor Company in Detroit in 1903, pioneering assembly line production and revolutionizing industrial manufacturing based on Automotive Hall of Fame archives and Michigan Historical Society records
The transformative industrial innovator originating from Detroit through manufacturing heritage connections is Henry Ford
